cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper deals with causal network inference, which involves analyzing time series data to infer the underlying network dynamic processes that produce such observations. This falls under the broad category of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the development of computational and data-efficient algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.SI (signal processing and machine learning) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper's focus on network-coupled dynamical systems suggests a potential fit with the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
